Citation.sTitle: Effect of temperature on the physical properties of two ionic liquids
Citation.sAbstract: Density, speed of sound, refractive index, and dynamic viscosity of the ionic liquids (ILs) 1-butyl-1-methylpyrrolidinium  bis(trifluoromethylsulfonyl)imide, BMpyr NTf2, and trihexyl(tetradecyl) phosphonium  dicyanamide, P66614 dca, were studied as a function of temperature at atmospheric pressure. Thermal  expansion coefficient, ap, molecular volumes, and standard entropies of these ILs were calculated from  the experimental density values. The solubility of three aromatic components (benzene, toluene, and ethylbenzene)  in the selected ILs was carried out at T = 298.15 K and atmospheric pressure and compared  with literature values for sulfolane.
sAuthor: Esperanca, J. M. S. S.[Jose M. S. S.]
